"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49440","Home Office","false","2014-05-12","<p> </p><p>While published statistics provide data on the number of Syrian's who have <br>applied for asylum in the UK (4,714 between 2001-2013), how many have been <br>granted refugee status (2,182) or refused (2,065) and how many have been <br>removed (305 between 2004 and 2013), it is not possible to confirm the total <br>number of refugees and asylum seekers from Syria resident in the UK.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49440/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49440/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49440/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49440/answer/previousversion/8888","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate she has made of the total number of refugees and asylum seekers from Syria resident in the UK.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","197480"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49441","Home Office","false","2014-05-12","<p> </p><p>The published available figures only relate to asylum seekers.<br><br>The latest published Home Office data shows that between 1 April 2011 and 31 <br>December 2013 there were 3,796 applications for asylum from Syrian nationals <br>(including main applicants and their dependants) in the UK. During the same <br>period, 2,507 Syrian nationals and dependants were granted leave to remain in <br>the UK, including asylum, humanitarian protection or discretionary leave. These <br>grant decisions do not all necessarily relate to applications made in the same <br>period. In addition, given the need to give each asylum claim careful <br>consideration on its merits, not all the asylum applications made during that <br>period will have received a decision during that time. <br><br>Eurostat data based on provisional management information shows that between 1 <br>April 2011 and 28 February 2014 there were 4,105 applications for asylum from <br>Syrian nationals (including main applicants and their dependants) in the UK. <br>Eurostat data on grants of asylum are only available annually. There are some <br>definitional differences between National Statistics published by the Home <br>Office on a quarterly basis and monthly figures published by Eurostat.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49441/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49441/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49441/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49441/answer/previousversion/8892","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many (a) asylum seekers and (b) refugees from Syria have applied for leave to remain since the start of the Syrian conflict; and how many such people have been granted leave to remain.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","197467"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49442","Home Office","false","2014-05-12","<p> </p><p>Between 1 January 2013 and 31 December 2013, the average length of time taken <br>for asylum seekers and refugees from Syria to have an initial interview was <br>28 days from initial claim.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49442/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49442/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49442/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49442/answer/previousversion/8891","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what average length of time is taken for asylum seekers and refugees from Syria to have an initial interview.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","197474"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49443","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-05-07","<p> </p><p>The Government has introduced new legislation to tackle irresponsible dog ownership, including extending the criminal offence of allowing a dog to be dangerously out of control to all places, increasing the maximum penalties for allowing a dog to become dangerously out of control and ensuring that the new measures to deal with anti-social behaviour will include such instances when they involve a dog. As announced on 6<sup>th</sup> February 2013, Defra is looking at making changes to the arrangements for seizure and kennelling of suspected dangerous dogs but there are noplans to review the effectiveness of the restrictions on keeping certain types of dogwhich are specifically bred for fighting.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49443/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49443/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49443/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if he will review the effectiveness of current legislation on banned breeds of dog.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","197473"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49444","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-05-07","<p>Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) officials have been in contact with the Home Office to remind them of the appropriate terminology for the Falkland Islands. All Government departments and agencies should refer to âthe Falkland Islands' in all instances. There is no evidence that incorrect terminology has been used other than in the isolated cases which the Honourable Member highlights. Therefore no cross-Departmental guidance has been issued.</p><p> </p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49444/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49444/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49444/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 17 March 2014, Official Report, column 413W, on Falkland Islands, if he will discuss the correct use of the name Falkland Islands with the Secretary of State for the Home Office; and given the misuse of the name by his Department in its internal guidance if he will now issue cross-Department guidance.","false","Biography information for Thomas Docherty","Dunfermline and West Fife","Thomas Docherty","197475"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49445","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-05-09","<p>There are no current plans for the Department to relocate staff or offices to Brighton.</p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-05-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49445/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49445/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49445/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if he will bring forward proposals to relocate (a) staff and (b) offices of his Department to Brighton; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","197452"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49446","Department of Health","false","2014-05-08","<p>The Department has no plans to relocate Departmental offices or staff to Brighton.</p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49446/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49446/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49446/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will bring forward proposals to relocate (a) staff and (b) offices of his Department to Brighton; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","197453"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49447","Home Office","false","2014-05-06","<p> </p><p>The Department has no plans to (a) relocate staff to Brighton and <br>(b) relocate offices to Brighton.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49447/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49447/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49447/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will bring forward proposals to relocate (a) staff and (b) offices of her Department to Brighton; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","197449"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49448","Cabinet Office","false","2014-05-12","<p>Staffing is kept under review but I have no plans to move Cabinet Office staff to Brighton.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49448/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49448/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49448/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will bring forward proposals to relocate (a) staff and (b) offices of his Department to Brighton; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","197450"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49449","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-05-12","<p> </p><p>Whilst noting the many virtues of Brighton, as recognised by the conferring of City status to the towns of Brighton and Hove by Her Majesty in 2000, I am afraid I have to disappoint my hon. Friend. My Department has no current plans to dig out our bucket and spade and move to the seaside.</p><p>Since May 2010, my Department's priority has been to rationalise our wider estate to reduce costs. This has seen the Department surrender six leasehold office properties through a combination of lease breaks and expiries generating net savings in the period of around Â£7 million per annum. The Department has also successfully sub-let surplus space across its leasehold office estate during the same period, reducing the overall property costs by around Â£11.1 million.</p><p>The Department has also negotiated the early surrender of Eland House and is shortly scheduled to relocate to 2 Marsham Street to share premises with the Home Office. This move will reduce our Department's running costs by a further Â£9 million a year and generate savings for the taxpayer of Â£220 million over the lifetime of the building's lease. This illustrates the scope for Government and, indeed, the public sector as a whole to make sensible savings through better property management.</p><p>However, I commend the hon. Member for his cheerleading of the City as a place to do business.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49449/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49449/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49449/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will bring forward proposals to relocate (a) staff and (b) offices of his Department to Brighton; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","197454"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49450","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-05-08","<p>The Department has no plans to bring forward such proposals.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49450/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49450/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49450/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will bring forward proposals to relocate (a) staff and (b) offices of his Department to Brighton; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","197451"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49451","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-05-12","<p>We do not have any plans at this time to relocate staff or offices to Brighton.</p><p> </p><p>BIS currently has one active property in Brighton, Crown House, which houses the Insolvency Service.</p><p> </p><p>Any future decisions to move staff and offices to Brighton would be led by the business needs of BIS which would be supported by the Property and Asset Management Team.</p>","Cardiff Central","Jenny Willott",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49451/answer","Biography information for Jenny Willott","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49451/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49451/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will bring forward proposals to relocate (a) staff and (b) offices of his Department to Brighton; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","197446"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49452","Cabinet Office","false","2014-05-12","<p>The Government has already reduced the number of public bodies by over 280. 185 bodies have been abolished.</p><p>This is the largest restructuring of public bodies in a generation, making the landscape smaller, more accountable and transparent, and offering better value for money to the public.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49452/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49452/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49452/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many quangos have been abolished since 2010; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","197456"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49453","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-05-12","<p>The Department of Energy and Climate Change have no plans to relocate either (a) staff or (b) offices to Brighton.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49453/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49453/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49453/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, if he will bring forward proposals to relocate (a) staff and (b) offices of his Department to Brighton; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","197457"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49454","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-05-14","<p> </p><p>There are no current plans for the Department to relocate staff or offices to Brighton.</p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49454/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49454/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49454/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will bring forward proposals to relocate (a) staff and (b) offices of his Department to Brighton; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","197444"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49455","Department for Education","false","2014-05-07","<p>The Department for Education does not plan to relocate its staff or offices to Brighton.</p><p>Following the Department's Estates Review in 2012, it was announced that the Department would rationalise the existing estate from 12 core sites to 6, while maximising the efficiency of the retained sites. This has now been accomplished and the 6 remaining properties are located in Coventry, Darlington, London, Manchester, Nottingham and Sheffield.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49455/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49455/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49455/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if he will bring forward proposals to relocate (a) staff and (b) offices of his Department to Brighton; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","197458"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49456","Department for International Development","false","2014-05-12","<p> </p><p>DFID currently has dual UK headquarters in London and Scotland. We have no plans to relocate staff to Brighton.</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49456/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49456/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49456/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, if she will bring forward proposals to relocate (a) staff and (b) offices of her Department to Brighton; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","197447"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49457","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-13","<p> </p><p>Although reducing and rationalising the Ministry of Justice estate could result in relocations, there is no centrally driven relocation target to this effect. Any relocation is done based on the operational needs of the Department. The Ministry of Justice currently has no plans to relocate its staff or offices to Brighton. The Ministry of Justice continues to work with the Government Property Unit to ensure that the Ministry of Justice estate operates in an efficient manner and represents value for money.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49457/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49457/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49457/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will bring forward proposals to relocate (a) staff and (b) offices of his Department to Brighton; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","197441"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49458","Department for Transport","false","2014-05-12","<p> </p><p>The Department for Transport is a federated organisation comprising DfT (Central), the headquarters functions responsible mainly for policy issues, and five executive agencies responsible for the delivery of various services.</p><p> </p><p>DfT Central has no current plans to relocate staff or offices to Brighton. The Department for Transport (including our Executive Agencies) will consider opportunities for relocation as they arise, for example, through departmental reorganisation and reviews of estates requirements.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49458/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49458/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49458/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will bring forward proposals to relocate (a) staff and (b) offices of his Department to Brighton; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","197442"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49459","Women and Equalities","false","2014-05-08","<p>The Department has no plans to bring forward such proposals.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49459/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49459/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49459/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Ministers for Women and Equalities, if she will bring forward proposals to relocate (a) staff and (b) offices of her Department to Brighton; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","197445"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49460","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-05-08","<p /> <p /> <p>At the present time, there are no plans to relocate a) Departmental staff and b) offices to Brighton.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49460/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49460/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49460/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will bring forward proposals to relocate (a) staff and (b) offices of his Department to Brighton; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","197443"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49461","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-05-12","<p /> <p /> <p>Of the top ten highest capped households at the end of March 2014, the average capped amount was Â£607 per week.</p><p> </p><p>More detailed information on the amount capped is not available as providing this information could identify individuals and would breach data confidentiality. Further information on the number of households capped by the amount capped is found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/benefit-cap-number-of-households-capped-to-january-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/benefit-cap-number-of-households-capped-to-january-2014</a> <br></p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49461/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49461/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49461/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the highest amount is that a single household has been capped as a result of the benefit cap.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","197600"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49462","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-05-14","<p>For existing automated systems, human control requires an authorised operator to set the pre-programmed parameters for the weapon system's operation. Authority to activate such systems is given only in full accordance with the targeting directive for a specific theatre of operations, targeting policy and rules of engagement which ensure adherence to international humanitarian law. <br><br>The decision to deploy a particular weapon system in any given theatre of operations depends upon the context of that operation. It would be unreasonable to deny our Armed Forces the option of using the most appropriate weapons (including systems that can be operated in automatic mode) to engage legitimate military targets.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49462/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49462/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49462/answer","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49462/answer/previousversion/9116","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","11","Defence","Defence","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how levels of human control are defined in use of the ballistic sensor-fused munition and other similar systems which can operate in automatic mode.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","197477"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49463","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-05-14","<p>The targeting process, not the weapon, takes discrimination, proportionality and precautions in attack into account. The decision whether to use lethal force against a legitimate military target is made through a rigorous targeting process, the targeting directive for a specific theatre of operations and rules of engagement which ensure adherence to international humanitarian law. <br><br>Since 1999, when the requirement to do so under the Geneva Conventions Additional Protocol I Article 36 came into effect for the UK, all new weapons, means and methods of warfare entering service have been subjected to a review in order to ensure they are capable of being used lawfully in armed conflict. The UK is committed to upholding the Geneva Conventions and encourages others to do the same.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49463/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49463/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49463/answer","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49463/answer/previousversion/9117","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","11","Defence","Defence","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what safeguards are deployed to prevent a sensor-fused munition operating in automatic mode from confusing a military target with a civilian target.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","197479"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49465","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-05-07","<p>The table below gives the total number, and notional value, of Renewable Obligation Certificates (ROCs) issued to the two RO-accredited stations in Wales between April and December 2013. The number and cost of ROCs issued to ground-mounted stations is a sub-set of the number of ROCs issued; there are currently no building-mounted stations in Wales accredited under the RO.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="3"><p>ROCs issued*</p></td><td colspan="3"><p>Value (Â£m â rounded to the nearest Â£100K)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>All Solar PV</p></td><td><p>Ground-mounted**</p></td><td><p>Building-mounted**</p></td><td><p>All Solar PV</p></td><td><p>Ground-mounted</p></td><td><p>Building-mounted</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>14,560</p></td><td><p>6,263</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>0.7</p></td><td><p>0.3</p></td><td><p>-</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em>* Between April and December 2013</em></p><p><em>** Stations accredited from 1 April 2013</em></p><p> </p><p>Information is not available below country level. No ROCs were redeemed by accredited solar PV stations in Wales prior to the 2013/14 financial year.</p><p>The value of a ROC is estimated as the buy-out price (Â£42.02) +10%. The total number of ROCs redeemed in 2013/14, and the final value of a ROC for that obligation period, will not be confirmed until October 2014. ROCs issued for the UK as a whole can be found in table ET 6.3, available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/energy-trends-section-6-renewables" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/energy-trends-section-6-renewables</a></p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49465/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49465/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49465/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what the total value is of renewable obligation certificates issued to generators for (a) roof- and (b) ground-mounted solar schemes that have been redeemed in (a) Llanelli constituency and (ii) each constituency in Wales.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","197561"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49466","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-05-07","<p>DECC does not have data on the area of land covered by solar farms. There are currently 2 solar sites in Wales supported under the renewables obligation (totalling 12.2MW) and 2 sites (totalling 5MW) under the feed-in tariff scheme (FiTs) that are classified as 'Stand-alone' and are over 1MW in size. Information below country level is not available for sites in the Renewables Obligation. The sites accredited under FiTs are located in Monmouthshire.</p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49466/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49466/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49466/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how many acres of land are covered by solar farms in (a) Carmarthenshire, (b) Llanelli constituency, (c) each constitunecy in Wales and (d) each county in Wales.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","197563"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49467","Department of Health","false","2014-05-07","<p>The Health and Social Care Transition Programme (HSCTP) was set up to implement the changes introduced under the Health and Social Care Act 2012. The programme was led by the Department and closed on 31 March 2013. All of the organisations in the new health and care system assumed full responsibilities and powers as set out in the Act from 1 April 2013.</p><p> </p><p>Any enduring responsibilities that transferred to the Secretary of State for Health, my right hon. Friend the member for South West Surrey (Mr Hunt), or NHS England from 1 April 2013 are being discharged as part of business as usual arrangements in each organisation. As the HSCTP has closed and the new organisations are in place, there are no longer any officials working on the transition to a new system.</p><p> </p><p>Further information on the overall cost of transition is available in the National Audit Office report âManaging the transition to the reformed health system' available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p>www.nao.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/10175-001-Managing-the-transition-to-the-reformed-health-system.pdf</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49467/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49467/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49467/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many officials in (a) his Department and (b) NHS England are working on the transition to a new system following the implementation of the Health and Social Care Act 2012; and what the cost was of employing such officials in the latest period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","197471"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49468","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-12","<p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government recognises the need for greater openness in the family justice system. The challenge is to open the system up to greater scrutiny while protecting those involved especially the welfare of children. Last year, the President of the Family Division issued practice guidance in relation to committal of individuals found in contempt of court to ensure that these proceedings should be held in open court. In January this year, the President issued guidance aimed at increasing the number of judgments in family proceedings which are published. We are grateful to the President for his work in this area.</p><p> </p><p>The guidance is available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.judiciary.gov.uk/Resources/JCO/Documents/Guidance/transparency-in-the-family-courts-jan2014.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.judiciary.gov.uk/Resources/JCO/Documents/Guidance/transparency-in-the-family-courts-jan2014.pdf</a></p>","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Simon Hughes",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49468/answer","Biography information for Simon Hughes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49468/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49468/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps he is taking to improve the openness and transparency of the proceedings and accountability of Family Court decisions.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","197514"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49469","Department for Education","false","2014-05-08","<p>The Government recognises that a father's role in his child's life is a very important one and legislation in the Children and Families Act 2014 reflects the importance of children having a continuing relationship with both of their parents following family separation, as long as it is safe and in the child's best interests.</p><p>We are also strengthening the way in which breaches of child arrangement orders are handled. Cases which are breached within the first 12 months of an order being made will in future return to court quickly and, wherever possible, to the judge who made the original order. Courts will also be able to make full use of powers to direct a parent who is in breach of an order to participate in an activity, for example a parenting programme, to address their behaviour.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49469/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49469/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49469/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps he is taking to ensure that fathers have appropriate access to or custody of their children following separation or divorce in cases where there is no risk to the child.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","197515"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49470","Department of Health","false","2014-05-12","<p>The UK National Screening Committee advises Ministers and the National Health Service in all four countries about all aspects of screening policy and supports implementation. It is currently reviewing the evidence for screening young people between the ages of 12 to 39 years for the major causes of sudden cardiac death. A public consultation will open shortly.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>NHS England is working with the Chief Coroner to discuss what the coronial system can do to help reduce sudden cardiac death in the young. As a result, the Chief Coroner has written to local Coroners asking them to make families of those who have died of the condition aware that it may be inherited, and encouraging them to contact either the British Heart Foundation, Cardiac Risk in the Young, or their general practitioner for testing and counselling.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49470/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49470/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49470/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent steps he has taken to raise awareness of the conditions that can lead to young sudden cardiac death and sudden death syndrome.","false","Biography information for Julian Sturdy","York Outer","Julian Sturdy","197438"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49471","Home Office","false","2014-05-14","<p> </p><p>This was a national issue and all ports were affected. The issue was rectified <br>as soon as possible, with national security our first priority at all times. An <br>urgent investigation is being conducted to examine the circumstances <br>surrounding this incident.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49471/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49471/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49471/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, which sites were affected by the failure of UK Border Agency computers at passport control on 30 April 2014; what steps she is taking to investigate and rectify the problem; and what assessment she has made of the reasons for the computer failure.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","197486"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49472","Department for International Development","false","2014-05-07","<p> </p><p>Ensuring that the Millennium Development Goals and Sustainable Development Goals are coherent with and are integrated into the development agendas of all UK Government departments is a priority for this Government. DFID Ministers and officials work closely with other Government departments and through the National Security Council, Cabinet and Cabinet sub-Committees to ensure development coherence across HMG.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49472/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49472/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49472/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps she is taking to ensure that the millennium development goals and sustainable development goals are coherent with and integrated into the development agendas of all government departments.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Murphy","East Renfrewshire","Mr Jim Murphy","197519"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49473","Department for International Development","false","2014-05-07","<p> </p><p>The UK government welcomes the fact that life expectancy is increasing in developing countries and wants to see this positive trend continue. However, DFID also recognises that this brings new challenges, which the post-2015 framework should address. The High Level Panel, co-chaired by the Prime Minister, acknowledged this in its report to the UN Secretary General through its call to âleave no one behind.'</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49473/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49473/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49473/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps she is taking to ensure that her Department gives full consideration to the increasing impact and challenges that ageing populations will place on national governments, civil society and relevant stakeholders (a) between 2015 and 2030 and (b) after 2030.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Murphy","East Renfrewshire","Mr Jim Murphy","197518"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49474","Department for International Development","false","2014-05-07","<p> </p><p>Despite remarkable progress, some countries are off-track to meet MDG targets. In response, the Government has increased development assistance to fragile states, driven forward work to help unlock the potential of girls and women and focused more resources on creating the jobs, investment and growth that emerging and frontier markets need to escape poverty.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49474/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49474/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49474/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps she is taking to ensure that there is a renewed focus on the millennium development goals which have not yet been attained.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Murphy","East Renfrewshire","Mr Jim Murphy","197494"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49475","Department for International Development","false","2014-05-07","<p> </p><p>No UK aid to Syria has been written off as nugatory expenditure.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49475/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49475/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49475/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what proportion of UK aid to Syria has been written off as nugatory expenditure.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Murphy","East Renfrewshire","Mr Jim Murphy","197489"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49476","Department for International Development","false","2014-05-07","<p> </p><p>According to the UN, there are over 320,000 school-age Syrian refugee children in Lebanon and over 200,000 in Jordan. We continue to be concerned about barriers to education for refugees from Syria, which is why I have set up the Â£50m âNo Lost Generation initiative' which is providing desperately needed help, including trauma counselling and education.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49476/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49476/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49476/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment she has made of the effectiveness of teaching provision available to Syrian refugee children in Lebanon and Jordan; and what assessment she has made of the effects of language barriers on the effectiveness of such provision.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Murphy","East Renfrewshire","Mr Jim Murphy","197490"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49477","Department for International Development","false","2014-05-12","<p> </p><p>The UK supports a focus on âleaving no one behindâ across the post-2015 framework, as was recommended by the High Level Panel which was co-Chaired by the Prime Minister.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49477/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49477/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49477/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what consideration she has given to the case for having a stand-alone, specific goal on inequality in the Sustainable Development Goals.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Murphy","East Renfrewshire","Mr Jim Murphy","197521"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49478","Department for International Development","false","2014-05-12","<p> </p><p>The UK is engaging fully in the UN Open Working Group where discussions on the next set of development goals are taking place. We continue to push strongly for the inclusion of targets in line with the Sustainable Energy for All initiative, including universal access to modern energy services by 2030.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49478/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49478/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49478/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps she is taking to ensure that access to safe, affordable energy in rural areas is being treated as a specific high-priority target in the formulation of the Sustainable Development Goals.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Murphy","East Renfrewshire","Mr Jim Murphy","197522"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49479","Department for Transport","false","2014-05-07","<p> </p><p> </p><p>Details of Ministerial meetings with external organisations are published every quarter and this information can be accessed on the GOV.UK website via the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/ministerial-transparency-data#meetings" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/ministerial-transparency-data#meetings</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49479/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49479/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49479/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many meetings he has had with each private hire vehicle operator since 2010.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","197534"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49480","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-05-07","<p /> <p /> <p>Universal Credit is being developed and delivered across the UK. As expected with a programme of this size, some travel is needed to ensure effective delivery of the programme. DWP has clear policies on travel and accommodation expenses to ensure costs are minimised</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>It is not possible, on the grounds of disproportionate cost, to separate out this expenditure between DWP staff and contractors working on the Universal Credit project.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49480/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49480/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49480/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much was spent by the universal credit project on (a) staff travel and (b) overnight accommodation and allowances in each month of 2014 to date.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","197591"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49481","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-05-07","<p>The Department has developed a clearly defined compliance monitoring regime which commits to an appropriate level of checking for each of the 40 Work Programme contract package areas.<br> <br> The compliance management team work closely with Work Programme performance managers to ensure clear factual information is available for consideration as part of monthly Contract Performance Reviews with providers.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49481/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49481/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49481/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps he takes to monitor whether Work Programme prime providers fulfil their minimum service standards; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","197589"
