"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49520","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-05-09","<p> </p><p>The independent evaluation of the Flood and Coastal Resilience Partnership Funding approach was published on 23 April 2014. The report is available on the Defra R&amp;Dwebpages at the following the link:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="http://randd.defra.gov.uk/Default.aspx?Menu=Menu&amp;Module=More&amp;Location=None&amp;ProjectID=18734&amp;FromSearch=Y&amp;Publisher=1&amp;SearchText=fd2663&amp;SortString=ProjectCode&amp;SortOrder=Asc&amp;Paging=10#Description" target="_blank">http://randd.defra.gov.uk/Default.aspx?Menu=Menu&amp;Module=More&amp;Location=None&amp;ProjectID=18734&amp;FromSearch=Y&amp;Publisher=1&amp;SearchText=fd2663&amp;SortString=ProjectCode&amp;SortOrder=Asc&amp;Paging=10#Description</a></p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-05-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49520/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49520/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49520/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what recent progress has been made on the review of partnership funding for flood defences; and when the results of this review will be published.","false","Biography information for Baroness McIntosh of Pickering","Thirsk and Malton","Miss Anne McIntosh","197579"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49521","Department of Health","false","2014-05-12","<p>A search of the Department's Ministerial correspondence database has identified no recent representations on the future of community hospitals. This Government believes the National Health Service should improve discharge from acute hospitals and increase access to care and treatment in the community.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49521/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49521/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49521/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent representations he has received on the future of community hospitals; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Baroness McIntosh of Pickering","Thirsk and Malton","Miss Anne McIntosh","197580"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49522","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-05-08","<p>The Ministry of Defence was grateful to the noble Lord, Lord Ashcroft for conducting what proved to be a very useful survey of the attitudes of the public and the Armed Forces towards each other. While there were many positive findings, of particular concern was the perception amongst a majority of the public that veterans would have physical or mental problems as a result of service. Lord Ashcroft described this as ânot only untrue, but damaging'.<br><br>The 2012 survey provided valuable insight into the relationship between the Armed Forces and the nation they serve. This relationship is at the heart of the Armed Forces Covenant, which we published in May 2011. A great deal has been achieved through this mechanism in the last few years across a wide range of areas, including healthcare, accommodation, education, and welfare.<br><br>We will go on looking at what more we can do for our Armed Forces, their families, and Veterans, to ensure that they continue to receive the recognition they deserve, and if necessary, whatever help they may require.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49522/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49522/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49522/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the implications for his department's policies of the findings of The Armed Forces & Society survey produced by Lord Ashcroft.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","197613"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49523","Department for Education","false","2014-05-07","<p>Information on the percentage of history lessons taught to pupils in years 7 to 13 by non-subject specialists is publicly-available online, and published in the Main Tables at the following links:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-workforce-in-england-november-2010-provisional" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-workforce-in-england-november-2010-provisional</a> (Table 14)</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-workforce-in-england-november-2011" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-workforce-in-england-november-2011</a> (Table 14)</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-workforce-in-england-november-2012" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-workforce-in-england-november-2012</a> (Table 14)</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-workforce-in-england-november-2013" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-workforce-in-england-november-2013</a> (Table 13)</p><p> </p><p>Data for 2009 is not available.</p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49523/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49523/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49523/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what proportion of history lessons were taught by non-subject specialists in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","197546"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49524","Department for Education","false","2014-05-07","<p>The Department for Education does not hold information on the individual topics which students elect to take in their GCSE and A level examinations. Information on the proportion of pupils attempting GCSE history is published in the 2009/10[1], 2010/11[2], 2011/12[3] and 2012/13[4] GCSE and equivalent results statistical first release.</p><p>Information on the number of entries in A level history is published in the 2012/13[5] A level statistical first release.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>[1]<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/gcse-and-equivalent-results-england-academic-year-2009-to-2010-revised" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/gcse-and-equivalent-results-england-academic-year-2009-to-2010-revised</a> (Table 9)</p><p> </p><p>[2]<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/revised-gcse-and-equivalent-results-in-england-academic-year-2010-to-2011" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/revised-gcse-and-equivalent-results-in-england-academic-year-2010-to-2011</a> (Table 9)</p><p> </p><p>[3]<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/revised-gcse-and-equivalent-results-in-england-academic-year-2011-to-2012" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/revised-gcse-and-equivalent-results-in-england-academic-year-2011-to-2012</a> (Table 9)</p><p> </p><p>[4]<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/gcse-and-equivalent-results-in-england-2012-to-2013-revised" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/gcse-and-equivalent-results-in-england-2012-to-2013-revised</a> (Table 9)</p><p> </p><p>[5]<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/a-level-and-other-level-3-results-england-2012-to-2013-revised" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/a-level-and-other-level-3-results-england-2012-to-2013-revised</a> (Table 14)</p><p> </p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","197548","2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49524/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49524/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49524/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate he has made of the proportion of secondary school students who studied the First World War as part of their (a) GCSE and (b) A-level studies in each year since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","197547"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49525","Department for Education","false","2014-05-07","<p>The Department for Education does not hold information on the individual topics which students elect to take in their GCSE and A level examinations. Information on the proportion of pupils attempting GCSE history is published in the 2009/10[1], 2010/11[2], 2011/12[3] and 2012/13[4] GCSE and equivalent results statistical first release.</p><p>Information on the number of entries in A level history is published in the 2012/13[5] A level statistical first release.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>[1]<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/gcse-and-equivalent-results-england-academic-year-2009-to-2010-revised" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/gcse-and-equivalent-results-england-academic-year-2009-to-2010-revised</a> (Table 9)</p><p> </p><p>[2]<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/revised-gcse-and-equivalent-results-in-england-academic-year-2010-to-2011" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/revised-gcse-and-equivalent-results-in-england-academic-year-2010-to-2011</a> (Table 9)</p><p> </p><p>[3]<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/revised-gcse-and-equivalent-results-in-england-academic-year-2011-to-2012" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/revised-gcse-and-equivalent-results-in-england-academic-year-2011-to-2012</a> (Table 9)</p><p> </p><p>[4]<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/gcse-and-equivalent-results-in-england-2012-to-2013-revised" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/gcse-and-equivalent-results-in-england-2012-to-2013-revised</a> (Table 9)</p><p> </p><p>[5]<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/a-level-and-other-level-3-results-england-2012-to-2013-revised" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/a-level-and-other-level-3-results-england-2012-to-2013-revised</a> (Table 14)</p><p> </p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","197547","2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49525/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49525/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49525/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate he has made of the proportion of secondary school students who studied the Second World War as part of their (a) GCSE and (b) A-level studies in each year since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","197548"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49526","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-05-07","<p> </p><p>The Department does not hold information on the number of children in existing supported housing tenancies; however this information is collected for new lettings. The new lettings data is collected in the CORE (Continuous Recording of Lettings and Sales), which reports there were 11,370 children (under 16 years) in the households who were let supported housing in England in 2012-13.</p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49526/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49526/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49526/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate he has made of the number of children aged under 16 years living in supported housing.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","197549"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49527","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-08","<p> </p><p> </p><p>In April 2013 Her Majesty's Inspectorate of Prisons (HMIP) submitted a response to the Government's Transforming Youth Custody consultation, which set out our proposals for Secure Colleges.<br> <br> The Government values the important role HMIP performs in inspecting custodial establishments. We are therefore legislating in the Criminal Justice and Courts Bill for HMIP, along with Ofsted, to have a duty to inspect Secure Colleges. <br> <br> On 10 March 2014, I met with the Chief Inspector of Prisons and the Government's proposals for Secure Colleges were discussed. In addition, my officials have had, and continue to have, discussions with the Chief Inspector's staff in order to develop, in conjunction with Ofsted, arrangements for the inspection of Secure Colleges.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49527/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49527/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49527/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what recent representations he has received from HM Chief Inspector of Prisons about his plans to introduce secure colleges.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","197550"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49528","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-14","<p> </p><p> </p><p>In April 2013 Ofsted submitted a response to the Government's Transforming Youth Custody consultation, which set out our proposals for Secure Colleges.<br><br>The Government values the important role Ofsted performs in inspecting the provision of support and education in the custodial estate for under-18s. We are therefore legislating in the Criminal Justice and Courts Bill for Ofsted, along with Her Majesty's Inspector for Prisons (HMIP, to have a duty to inspect Secure Colleges.<br><br></p><p>My officials have regular discussions with Ofsted in relation to the inspection of youth custody, and are discussing with them, in conjunction with HMIP, arrangements for the inspection of Secure Colleges.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49528/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49528/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49528/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what recent representations he has received from Ofsted on his plans to introduce secure colleges.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","197625"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49529","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-05-07","<p>The latest results from the DECC Public Attitudes Tracking survey, published on 29 April 2014, show strong levels of public support for solar photovoltaic, with current support levels at 85%. In previous surveys solar PV has consistently scored 81% or above. However, these figures relate to support for solar PV in general, rather than any specific form of solar energy generation. In addition, the survey does not include any reference to large-scale or ground-based solar.</p><p> </p><p>The Government said in the UK Solar PV Strategy Part 2, published on 4 April 2014, that we are considering the implications of current trends of deployment in solar PV on the financial incentives available in Great Britain under the Renewables Obligation and small-scale Feed-in-Tariff. We will issue a public consultation shortly proposing changes to financial support for solar PV. The proposals on which we will be consulting are intended to take effect from the 2015/16 financial year.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49529/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49529/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49529/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what recent assessment he has made of levels of public support for solar photovoltaic; and if he will make it his policy that there will be no changes to the level of support available for large-scale solar under the Renewable Obligation scheme until at least April 2015.","true","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","197578"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49530","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-05-12","<p> </p><p> </p><p>We have identified around 1,400 cases subject to case closure which have child maintenance arrears based wholly or partly on an interim maintenance assessment.</p><p> </p><p>The arrears existing on cases coming up for closure will be reviewed, and where necessary revised, to ensure accuracy. Both parents will be informed of the arrears balance prior to their case closing.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49530/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49530/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49530/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate his Department has made of the number of Child Support Agency cases subject to case closure which have child maintenance arrears based wholly or partly on an interim maintenance assessment; and what steps he is taking to re-evaluate the amount of arrears owed and to inform the non-resident parent and parent with care accordingly.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","197481"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49531","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-05-12","<p /> <p /> <p>The powers available within Section 4(1) of the Child Support Information Regulations 2008 are used as part of the normal trace process available to caseworkers when required. However, this information is not routinely recorded for management information purposes. To provide this would require the creation of new information, which could only be completed and appropriately assured at a disproportionate cost.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49531/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49531/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49531/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how often powers in the Child Support Information Regulations 2008 to require suppliers of gas and electricity to (a) provide the Child Support Agency with information to confirm the whereabouts of a non-resident parent and (b) obtain account information to assist enforcement action to recover child maintenance arrears have been used to date.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","197482"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49532","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-05-07","<p /> <p /> <p>There were no claims to the Independent Living Fund in the last year as the Fund was closed to new applications in 2010.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49532/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49532/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49532/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many claims to the Independent Living Fund of what total value were made in each parliamentary constituency in the last year.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","197483"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49533","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-05-07","<p /> <p /> <p>The information is not available in the format requested as the ILF does not record the employment status of its recipients.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49533/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49533/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49533/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of recipients of the Independent Living Fund (a) are in employment and (b) were in employment at the date of application.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","197574"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49534","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-05-07","<p> </p><p>Decisions on rateable values are made independently of Ministers by the Valuation Office Agency. All rateable values are based on the rental value of the property and for public houses rates are based on actual rents paid by tenants. Ratepayers should contact the Valuation Office Agency if they are concerned about their rateable value and may appeal to the independent Valuation Tribunal if their dispute cannot be resolved.</p><p>As part of our review of business rates administration, the Government will consider options for arriving at a rental based assessment for non-domestic properties including public houses and the discussion paper, published last month, invites views on this issue.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49534/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49534/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49534/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the effect on the viability of public houses of the method by which business rates are currently calculated.","false","Biography information for Charlotte Leslie","Bristol North West","Charlotte Leslie","197572"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49535","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-05-07","<p> </p><p>In the new planning guidance, launched on 6 March, we have made it crystal clear that councils need to consider the strict tests set out in national policy and, where these are not met new development should not be allowed. These tests, set out in the National Planning Policy Framework, include ensuring new development does not increase flood risk elsewhere. The tests are designed to protect people and property from flooding and give councils the robust ability to reject unacceptable planning applications.</p><p>We also expect Strategic Flood Risk Assessments, prepared by local councils to inform Local Plans, to consider flood risks to and from surrounding areas in the same flood catchment.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49535/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49535/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49535/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what guidance his Department gives local authorities on considering the potential flooding risks to land in neighbouring local authorities when making planning decisions.","false","Biography information for Charlotte Leslie","Bristol North West","Charlotte Leslie","197573"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49536","Department of Health","false","2014-05-07","<p>The Department does not collect data about how much each National Health Service trust and foundation trust spends on legal costs on individual employment cases.</p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49536/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49536/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49536/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how much each NHS trust and foundation trust spent on legal costs on individual employment cases in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Charlotte Leslie","Bristol North West","Charlotte Leslie","197595"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49537","Department of Health","false","2014-05-07","<p>There is currently already provision in the Medical Act 1983 (s.49) which makes it an offence for a person to pretend to be or use the title âsurgeonâ which implies registration with the General Medical Council.</p><p> </p><p>However, as part of a longer title, the title âsurgeonâ has not been restricted and is widely used for other specialist employment roles e.g. tree surgeon, veterinary surgeon etc.</p><p> </p><p>The Law Commission has recommended in its report on the regulation of health care professionals and social care professionals in England, published April 2014, that the Government should consider undertaking a full review of existing protected titles and functions, and related offences. We will consider the Law Commission's proposals and produce a formal response in due course.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49537/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49537/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49537/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what his policy is on making the term surgeon a protected title.","false","Biography information for Charlotte Leslie","Bristol North West","Charlotte Leslie","197513"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49538","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-05-07","<p>This is a complex investigation that the Environment Agency is working hard to complete. Legal challenges to the investigation in the civil courts have caused delays. Once the investigation is complete and the matter has been legally reviewed, the Environment Agency will decide on any appropriate enforcement.</p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49538/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49538/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49538/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when the Environment Agency expects to conclude its investigation into Churngold Recycling Ltd.","false","Biography information for Charlotte Leslie","Bristol North West","Charlotte Leslie","197571"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49539","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-05-07","<p>The Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Richmond (Yorks) (Mr Hague) spoke to the Nigerian Foreign Minister on 18 April when he condemned the abductions and offered UK assistance in securing the release of the schoolgirls.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Mark Simmonds",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49539/answer","Biography information for Mark Simmonds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49539/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49539/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his Nigerian counterpart on the recent kidnapping of schoolgirls from Chibok, Nigeria.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian Lucas","197470"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49540","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-05-07","<p>Since the abduction of the Nigerian school girls on 14 April we have remained in close contact with the Nigerian authorities about the case. Although the whereabouts of the girls remains unclear, reports in the media and from girls who escaped suggest they are being held in the Sambisa Forest area of Borno State. Media reports also suggest the girls may have been taken into Cameroon and Chad. We continue to try and establish the facts in this case.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Mark Simmonds",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49540/answer","Biography information for Mark Simmonds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49540/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49540/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what reports he has received on the current whereabouts of the children recently kidnapped from Chibok, Nigeria.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian Lucas","197469"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49541","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-05-07","<p>Since the abduction of the Nigerian school girls on 14 April, our High Commission in Abuja has remained in close contact with the Nigerian authorities. The Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Richmond (Yorks) (Mr Hague) offered our assistance when he spoke to the Nigerian Foreign Minister on 18 April. So far we have not received a formal request for assistance from the Nigerian Government.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Mark Simmonds",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49541/answer","Biography information for Mark Simmonds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49541/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49541/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what requests for assistance the Government has received in connection with the recent kidnappings from Chibok, Nigeria.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian Lucas","197472"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49542","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-05-07","<p>There are ongoing interactions at senior level between Ministers in the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS) and senior executives from both AstraZeneca and Pfizer as part of the Department's wider interactions with the Life Sciences industry.</p><p> </p><p>BIS Ministers have spoken with the Chief Executives and others from both companies in the last couple of weeks about recent market developments including the approaches from Pfizer to AstraZeneca.</p><p> </p>","Havant","Mr David Willetts",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49542/answer","Biography information for Lord Willetts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49542/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49542/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what discussions either orally or in writing he or his Ministers or officials in his Department have had with (a) Pfizer and (b) AstraZeneca in the last two months regarding any bid for AstraZeneca.","false","Biography information for Ann McKechin","Glasgow North","Ann McKechin","197493"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49543","Prime Minister","false","2014-05-07","<p>We are committed to ensuring that the life sciences sector in this country continues to flourish and grow, with the UK at the forefront of life sciences R&amp;D, and retaining our role as a leading manufacturing base. While ultimately the potential takeover bid is a matter for the respective boards and shareholders of the two companies, Ministers and officials across Government have engaged with both companies to ensure that the outcome is positive for the long-term future of this sector in the UK.</p><p> </p><p>I also refer the hon. Member to the answers I gave at Prime Minister's Questions today.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron","197492","2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49543/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49543/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49543/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, what criteria he used to select those who he has instructed to review any bid for AstraZeneca.","false","Biography information for Ann McKechin","Glasgow North","Ann McKechin","197491"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49544","Prime Minister","false","2014-05-07","<p>We are committed to ensuring that the life sciences sector in this country continues to flourish and grow, with the UK at the forefront of life sciences R&amp;D, and retaining our role as a leading manufacturing base. While ultimately the potential takeover bid is a matter for the respective boards and shareholders of the two companies, Ministers and officials across Government have engaged with both companies to ensure that the outcome is positive for the long-term future of this sector in the UK.</p><p> </p><p>I also refer the hon. Member to the answers I gave at Prime Minister's Questions today.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron","197491","2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49544/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49544/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49544/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, what discussions either orally or in writing he or his Ministers or officials have had with (a) Pfizer and (b) AstraZeneca in the last two months regarding any bid for AstraZeneca.","false","Biography information for Ann McKechin","Glasgow North","Ann McKechin","197492"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49545","Department of Health","false","2014-05-07","<p>The following table lists the number of staff currently employed to work on competition issues in the Department, NHS England and Monitor.</p><p> </p><p>The level of spend on employing staff to work on competition issues in each of the last five years could only be provided at a disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Organisation</p></td><td><p>Number of Staff Employed</p></td><td><p>Cost of employing such staff in 2013-14</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Department of Health</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>Â£98,760-Â£121,814<sup>1</sup></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>NHS England</p></td><td><p>0 full time posts</p></td><td><p>n/a</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Monitor<sup>2</sup></p></td><td><p>30</p></td><td><p>Â£1,588,554</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><em>Notes:</em></p><p><sup>1</sup> The figures shown are the combined cost of the paybands for the 2 staff.</p><p><sup>2</sup>Monitor's competition functions were established by the Health and Social Care Act 2012. In the transition year 2012-13 Monitor hosted the Cooperation and Competition Panel at a cost of Â£1,068,099</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49545/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49545/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49545/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many staff are employed in (a) his Department, (b) NHS England and (c) Monitor to undertake work on or relating to competition issues; and what the cost of employing such staff was in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","197535"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49546","Department of Health","false","2014-05-12","<p>Mental health and wellbeing, for both adults and children, is a priority for this Government. Our overarching goal is to ensure that mental health has equal priority with physical health, and that everyone who needs it has timely access to the best available treatment. We have enshrined in law the equal status of mental and physical health in the Health and Social Care Act 2012.</p><p> </p><p>The Mandate to NHS England makes clear that 'everyone who needs it should have timely access to evidence based services'. This will involve extending and ensuring more open access to the Improving Access to Psychological Therapies programme, in particular for children and young people, and for those out of work.</p><p> </p><p>We are also committed to introducing access and/or waiting time standards for mental health. The revised Mandate asks NHS England to develop and evaluate a range of costed options to implement access and waiting standards for mental health services starting from April 2015, with a phased introduction depending on affordability.</p><p> </p><p>We will hold the National Health Service to account for the quality of services and outcomes for mental health patients through the NHS Outcomes Framework. Improvements for people with mental health problems will also be a crucial element of success across the framework as a whole.</p><p> </p><p>Our action plan, <em>Closing the Gap</em>, which was launched in January 2014, sets our priorities for action and progress in mental health services over the next couple of years, including actions supporting commissioners in allocating resources.</p><p> </p><p>We are setting up a new, national Mental Health Intelligence Network to provide comprehensive, up to date information about mental health and wellbeing, mental health problems and what the most pressing needs are in each area â which will support commissioning of services.</p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49546/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49546/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49546/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that resources for mental health services meet the requirements of both adults and children.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","197541"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49547","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-05-12","<p>My Rt. Hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills launched a consultation on proposals to tackle abuses in the use of zero hours contracts. The consultation was launched on 19 December 2013, closed on 13 March 2014 and received over 30,000 responses.</p><p> </p><p>The Government response to the consultation will be published in due course.</p>","Cardiff Central","Jenny Willott",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49547/answer","Biography information for Jenny Willott","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49547/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49547/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what recent steps he has taken to ensure that zero-hour contracts are not used in an exploitative manner.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","197555"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49548","Department for Education","false","2014-05-08","<p>The revised school food standards will apply to single mainstream academies and free schools opening from July 2014, other mainstream academies and free schools opening from autumn 2014 and non-mainstream academies opening later in 2014. Academies set up prior to 2010 already have to comply.</p><p>During their review of school food, the authors of the School Food Plan approached several academy chains, including the Harris Federation, the Oasis Community Learning Multi-Academy Trust, and the School Partnership Trust. All agreed in principle to comply with the standards and the Leon Foundation are encouraging as many academies and free schools as possible to sign up formally to the new standards.</p><p>99% of those academies which responded to a survey by the School Food Trust in 2012 said they were committed to following the new food standards.</p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49548/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49548/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49548/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if he will take steps to ensure that school lunches in academies and free schools meet the nutritional standards of those in the state sector; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","197552"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49549","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-14","<p> </p><p> </p><p>We will carefully consider the Ombudsman's recommendations made in the Learning Lessons Bulletin on Risk Factors in self-inflicted deaths in prison to identify further learning. I also refer the honourable member to the answer given to the Lord's Oral Question on 6 February 2014 (<em>Official report Col 36 )</em>, announcing that the Government hasestablished an Independent Review into the self-inflicted deaths of 18-24 year olds in NOMS custody. The review is being led by Lord Harris of Haringey and will report by Spring 2015. NOMS takes the safety of prisoners very seriously and draws learning from individual death in custody reports from the PPO as quickly as possible.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49549/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49549/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49549/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps his Department is taking to implement the recommendations of the Prison and Probation Ombudsman's (PPO) report on Learning from PPO Investigations: Risk factors in self-inflicted deaths in prisons.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","197587"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49550","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-14","<p> </p><p> </p><p>A Gold Command Suite (GCS) is located at National Offender Management Service (NOMS) headquarters in London. It provides strategic assistance in the managing of serious prison incidents to the Governor of a prison in England and Wales.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Reason</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011-12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012-13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013-14</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Hostage</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>27</p></td><td><p>54</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Concerted indiscipline</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>13</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Escape</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>Industrial Action</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>Barricade</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>Civil Disturbances</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>At Height</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>11</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Fire</p></td><td> </td><td><p>1</p></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>Barricade</p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Miscellaneous</p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>32</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>43</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>81</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Although there has been an increase in the number of times the GCS was opened, the number of callouts of Tornado staff (a mutual aid arrangement between prisons who respond to the most serious incidents that cannot be managed locally) is half of what it was in 2007. There has been no rise in the number of serious incidents being attended.</p><p> </p><p>A large part of the increase in the number of times the GCS was opened was for hostage incidents. Many incidents that we manage as âhostageâ we believe to be acts of collusion between the alleged perpetrator and victim(s) in attempts to have their demands met. NOMS National Tactical Response Group, which has the specialist skills required to deal with such incidents, is frequently called to attend as a precautionary measure. Many of these incidents are dealt with very quickly with minimal disruption to the prison.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49550/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49550/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49550/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, on how many occasions the Prison Service Gold Command has been opened in each of the last 36 months; and what the nature was of each incident that caused it to be opened.","false","Biography information for Heidi Alexander","Lewisham East","Heidi Alexander","197468"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49551","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-07","<p> </p><p> </p><p>On release from custody, offenders who meet the referral criteria may be accommodated in an Approved Premises (AP). (APs were formerly known as Probation &amp; Bail Hostels.)There are 100 APs in England &amp; Wales, providing supervised accommodation for offenders under probation supervision. They also house a small number of defendants on bail.</p><p> </p><p>Most APs are managed by probation trusts and funded out of the total grant paid to the trust by the National Offender Management Service. The AP element is not separately identified. Because of this funding arrangement, it is not possible to provide the information requested without incurring disproportionate cost.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49551/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49551/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49551/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what his most recent estimate is of the average cost of housing an individual in (a) a probation hostel and (b) approved premises for 12 months.","false","Biography information for Heidi Alexander","Lewisham East","Heidi Alexander","197611"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49552","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-08","<p> </p><p>Providing a detailed response to these questions will require officials to manually collate data. This cannot be accomplished in the time available. My honourable friend Shailesh Vara will therefore write with a detailed response as soon as possible, and will place a copy of this letter in the library of the house.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49552/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49552/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49552/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many court buildings which were not counted as closed had fewer than five cases listed for each week in the preceding (a) three, (b) six and (c) 12 months at 31 March 2014; and what the location was of each such building.","false","Biography information for Richard Fuller","Bedford","Richard Fuller","197539"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49553","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-08","<p> </p><p>Providing a detailed response to these questions will require officials to manually collate data. This cannot be accomplished in the time available. My honourable friend Shailesh Vara will therefore write with a detailed response as soon as possible, and will place a copy of this letter in the library of the house.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49553/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49553/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49553/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many court buildings which were not counted as closed had no cases listed in the preceding (a) three, (b) six and (c) 12 months at 31 March 2014; and what the location was of each such building.","false","Biography information for Richard Fuller","Bedford","Richard Fuller","197536"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49554","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-08","<p> </p><p>Providing a detailed response to these questions will require officials to manually collate data. This cannot be accomplished in the time available. My honourable friend Shailesh Vara will therefore write with a detailed response as soon as possible, and will place a copy of this letter in the library of the house.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49554/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49554/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49554/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate he has made of the annual cost to the public purse of maintaining court buildings which are not listed as closed and which have no cases listed for (a) three, (b) six and (c) 12 months.","false","Biography information for Richard Fuller","Bedford","Richard Fuller","197537"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49555","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-08","<p> </p><p>Providing a detailed response to these questions will require officials to manually collate data. This cannot be accomplished in the time available. My honourable friend Shailesh Vara will therefore write with a detailed response as soon as possible, and will place a copy of this letter in the library of the house.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49555/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49555/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49555/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate he has made of the annual cost to the public purse of maintaining court buildings which are not listed as closed and which had fewer than five cases listed each week for (a) three, (b) six and (c) 12 months.","false","Biography information for Richard Fuller","Bedford","Richard Fuller","197538"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49781","Department for Transport","false","2014-05-08","<p> </p><p>In addition to the Â£278m of funding directly for cycling in England, we continue to support Bikeability cycle training for children. It provides trainees with skills suited to the road, but also explains the importance of obeying the Highway Code, and sharing the road. Some councils provide free or subsidised training to adults.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49781/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49781/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49781/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to encourage safer cycling.","false","Biography information for Jesse Norman","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","903904"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49797","Department for Transport","false","2014-05-08","<p> </p><p>The Government continues to monitor the publically available sources of data on motor insurance premiums. The Government's reforms to civil litigation costs and funding will result in unnecessary and excessive costs being removed from the system. However, the level and timing of any reduction in such premiums is a matter for the insurance industry itself.</p><p>We are working with insurers to mitigate fraud, excessive whiplash claims and young drivers risk to reduce premiums further.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49797/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49797/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49797/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of Government policy on the level of car insurance premiums.","false","Biography information for Mr David Ward","Bradford East","Mr David Ward","903899"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50200","Department for Transport","false","2014-05-08","<p> </p><p>The Government takes cycle safety very seriously. In this Parliament we have committed Â£278m of funding directly for cycling in England; this includes junction safety schemes and traffic free and traffic calmed routes.</p><p> </p><p>We have also made it easier for local authorities to implement 20 mph zones and other highway measures to support cycle safety, and we encourage them to consider these measures on their highway network.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50200/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50200/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/50200/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-05-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to improve road safety for cyclists.","false","Biography information for Charlotte Leslie","Bristol North West","Charlotte Leslie","903890"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49175","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-05-14","<p>It has not proved possible to respond to the hon. Member in the time available before Prorogation.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49175/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49175/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49175/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will make it his policy that a war widow's pension is provided for life to those awarded such a pension between 31 March 1973 and 5 April 2005.","false","Biography information for Chris Williamson","Derby North","Chris Williamson","197342"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49176","Department for International Development","false","2014-05-08","<p> </p><p>The UN Sustainable Energy for All initiative estimated that in 2010 only 32% of people in sub-Saharan Africa had access to electricity. There is high potential for household scale systems using sustainable and renewable energy such as solar power to increase access to electricity.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>DFID will match funding for Solar Aid's SunnyMoney appeal in the Guardian Newspaper. This will fund the distribution of portable solar lights through Solar Aid's social enterprise âSunnyMoney Way,' in Zambia, Malawi, Kenya and Uganda. Through this project, Solar Aid expect to distribute some 76,400 solar lights benefiting over 400,000 people.</p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49176/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49176/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49176/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment she has made of the potential contribution of sustainable lighting systems to development in Africa; and if her Department will collaborate with Solar Aid to provide such systems to communities in Africa.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","197345"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49177","Department for International Development","false","2014-05-08","<p> </p><p>DFID recognises the important role that the private sector plays in developing and delivering products to increase access to energy in poor countries. DFID make funding available to energy in Africa. This includes the Renewable Energy and Adaptation to Climate Change (REACT) window of the Africa Enterprise Challenge Fund.</p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49177/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49177/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49177/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, if her Department will provide support to the Bright Green Energy Group for distributing solar energy systems to rural communities in Bangladesh.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","197344"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49178","Prime Minister","false","2014-05-06","<p>There is a strong consensus in the global scientific community that nuclear energy represents one of the lowest carbon forms of baseload electricity generation.</p><p> </p><p /> <p>The UN Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC) estimates that the life cycle emissions associated with the generation of electricity from nuclear power groups are 16g CO<sub>2</sub> per kWh electricity produced. This is very low compared to the equivalent figure for electricity produced by natural gas turbines, which is in excess of 400g CO<sub>2</sub>/kWh, and similar to the IPCC's estimate for widespread non-baseload form of electricity generation, such as wind.</p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p>The Parliamentary Office of Science and Technology report âCarbon Footprint of Electricity Generation' states that the operation of the nuclear power station accounts for less than 1% of the total life cycle emissions of nuclear electricity generation.</p><p /> <p> </p><p> </p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49178/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49178/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49178/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, pursuant to his oral Answer of 30 April 2014, Official Report, column 824, what the evidential basis is for the statement that nuclear power is carbon-free.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","197381"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49179","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-05-06","<p>Our Embassy in Tel Aviv raises complaints where British nationals appear to have been subjected to differential treatment by Israeli border control on the basis of their race or ethnicity with the Israeli Ministry of Foreign Affairs.</p>","Faversham and Mid Kent","Hugh Robertson",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49179/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugh Robertson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49179/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49179/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions his Department has had with Israeli authorities on discrimination against UK citizens of Palestinian or Arab origin by Israeli border control.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","197383"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49180","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-05-06","<p>We have not made any representations to the Israeli authorities on this issue.</p>","Faversham and Mid Kent","Hugh Robertson",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49180/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugh Robertson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49180/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49180/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he has made representations to the Israeli government on extending to UK citizens of Palestinian origin visiting Israel similar concessions to those Israel has offered to the US administration in exchange for Israel's entry to the US visa waiver scheme.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","197379"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49181","Department of Health","false","2014-05-08","<p>The National Institute for Health Research (NIHR) funded the NIHR Collaboration for Leadership in Applied Health Research and Care (CLAHRC) for South Yorkshire from 2008 to 2013. The CLAHRC carried out a programme of research on young people with Type 1 diabetes including research relating to eating disorders in this patient group. Outputs include papers published in the journal <em>Diabetic Medicine</em>.</p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49181/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49181/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49181/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what research his Department has commissioned on diabulimia in teenagers and young adults.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","197377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49182","Department for International Development","false","2014-05-08","<p> </p><p>No such assessment has been possible. UK aid helps to finance the Palestinian Authority's fiscal deficit, which would significantly decrease if Israeli movement and access restrictions in the OPTs were lifted. The World Bank estimates that if Israeli restrictions were lifted in âArea C' of the West Bank alone, the Palestinian economy would expand by more than a third and potentially would not require international donor assistance.</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49182/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49182/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49182/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what estimate she has made of the additional costs resulting from Israeli border, access and planning controls to UK-funded development projects in the Occupied Palestinian Territories.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","197380"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49183","Department for International Development","false","2014-05-08","<p> </p><p>DFID and the EU regularly lobby Israel against the illegal demolition of Palestinian homes and infrastructure, and the forced transfer of people in Area C and East Jerusalem.</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49183/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49183/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49183/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what discussions she has had with the European Commission and her counterparts in EU member states on compensation requests to Israeli authorities for EU-funded aid projects demolished by the Israeli authorities.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","197408"
