"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49185","Department of Health","false","2014-05-08","<p>The International Conference on Harmonisation (ICH) Note for Guidance on Good Clinical Practice (GCP) is an international standard for GCP. It became operational in the European Union in January 1997 and is a set of internationally recognised ethical and scientific quality requirements which must be observed for designing, conducting, recording and reporting clinical trials that involve the participation of human subjects. This guidance is available on the web and is published on the Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency's (MHRA) website. In addition the MHRA published the MHRA Good Clinical Practice Guide in September 2013.</p><p> </p><p>The Health Research Authority (HRA) publishes a range of resources on research ethics that have relevance to clinical trials sponsored by pharmaceutical companies. These resources are available on the HRA website at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.hra.nhs.uk/resources/" target="_blank">www.hra.nhs.uk/resources/</a></p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49185/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49185/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49185/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what guidance his Department publishes for pharmaceutical companies to ensure that the clinical trials they conduct are carried out ethically and safely.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","197308"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49186","Department of Health","false","2014-05-08","<p>Prior to April 2013, primary care trusts were responsible for dealing with individual funding requests and information on individual funding request decisions, or on the time taken to consider such requests, was not collected centrally.</p><p> </p><p>From April 2013, NHS England assumed responsibility for commissioning adult specialist neurosciences services, including the majority of services for patients with Parkinson's disease, with some being the responsibility of clinical commissioning groups.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has informed us that information on the number of individual funding requests made to NHS England is not currently available. NHS England is improving its data collection mechanisms and aims to improve availability of such information in the future.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has advised us it aims to inform the requesting clinician of the outcome of the individual funding request panel decision within 40 working days from the date of receipt of a completed request form. There are no plans to collect information on the average time taken for these decisions to be made.</p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","197326","2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49186/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49186/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49186/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many individual funding requests for the prescription of Duodopa to patients with Parkinson's disease were (a) made, (b) accepted, (c) accepted following an appeal and (d) rejected in (i) 2011-12, (ii) 2012-13 and (iii) 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","197325"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49187","Department of Health","false","2014-05-08","<p>Prior to April 2013, primary care trusts were responsible for dealing with individual funding requests and information on individual funding request decisions, or on the time taken to consider such requests, was not collected centrally.</p><p> </p><p>From April 2013, NHS England assumed responsibility for commissioning adult specialist neurosciences services, including the majority of services for patients with Parkinson's disease, with some being the responsibility of clinical commissioning groups.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has informed us that information on the number of individual funding requests made to NHS England is not currently available. NHS England is improving its data collection mechanisms and aims to improve availability of such information in the future.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has advised us it aims to inform the requesting clinician of the outcome of the individual funding request panel decision within 40 working days from the date of receipt of a completed request form. There are no plans to collect information on the average time taken for these decisions to be made.</p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","197325","2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49187/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49187/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49187/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the average waiting time is for a decision on an individual funding request for the prescription of Duodopa to a patient with Parkinson's disease.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","197326"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49188","Department of Health","false","2014-05-08","<p>We have made no such assessments.</p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","197328","2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49188/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49188/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49188/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment his Department has made of potential geographical variations in the handling of individual funding requests for the prescription of Duodopa to patients with Parkinson's disease.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","197327"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49189","Department of Health","false","2014-05-08","<p>We have made no such assessments.</p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","197327","2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49189/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49189/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49189/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment his Department has made of time spent by clinicians on producing and administering individual funding requests for the prescription of Duodopa to patients with Parkinson's disease.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","197328"
