"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49242","Department for Education","false","2014-05-07","<p>The Department for Education does not hold the information requested.</p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49242/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49242/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49242/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the average cost of a primary school meal was in 2013.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","197434"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49243","Department for Education","false","2014-05-07","<p>The Department for Education does not hold information on how many childcare places for disadvantaged two-year-olds have been created since September 2013. Local authorities are responsible for ensuring that every eligible child, whose parents want a childcare place, is able to take one. We are reforming the early education market so that places are both more affordable and accessible. We are encouraging more schools to provide places for two-year-olds, including as part of an offer of provision between 8am and 6pm. The introduction of childminder agencies will also provide a new way for parents to find places that are suited to their needs.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49243/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49243/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49243/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many childcare places for disadvantaged two year olds have been created since September 2013.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","197435"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49244","Department for Education","false","2014-05-07","<p>This information is not held centrally.</p><p> </p><p>In his autumn statement, the Chancellor of the Exchequer announced over Â£1 billion revenue funding for universal free school meals for pupils in reception, year 1 and year 2 between 2014 and 2016. This funding, which includes special provision of Â£22.5 million for small schools in 2014-15, will be used by schools to pay for the cost of producing school lunches for newly eligible pupils, including any additional staff required.</p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49244/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49244/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49244/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate he has made of the number of additional catering staff needed in schools to deliver the extension of free school meals to all pupils in reception, year 1 and year 2 in September 2014.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","197436"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49245","Department for Education","false","2014-05-09","<p>In February 2014, local authorities reported that around 103,000 two-year-olds were already accessing a funded early learning place. Of these, around 95,000 were from the 20% most disadvantaged cohort, which represents 73%.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2014-05-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49245/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49245/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49245/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate he has made of the (a) number and (b) proportion of the 20 per cent most disadvantaged two year olds who are currently taking up their free childcare place.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","197433"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49246","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-05-08","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the answer I gave on 31 March 2014, Official Report, column 463W, to the Hon. Member for Bristol East (Kerry McCarthy) regarding the UNESCO Convention on Underwater Cultural Heritage. The UK is already a State Party to the United Nations Convention on the Law of the Sea.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49246/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49246/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49246/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment his Department has made of whether to become a signatory to the UNESCO Convention on Underwater Cultural Heritage and the International Law of the Sea.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","197238"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49247","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-05-06","<p> </p><p> </p><p>Subject to Royal Assent of the Pensions Bill a duty will be placed on the Secretary of State to make regulations to allow service spouses and civil partners, due to reach State Pension age from 6 April 2016, to apply for National Insurance credits for periods during which they accompanied their husband, wife or civil partner on a posting outside the UK. The regulations will make provision to allow credits for periods between 1975/76 and 2010.</p><p> </p><p>We are working with the Ministry of Defence on the finer details of the scheme including the manner in which applications will need to be made and the precise date when the administrative arrangements will be in place.</p><p> </p><p>We estimate that up to 20,000 individuals could have a higher single-tier pension from these credits as some individuals may, at state pension age, already have sufficient qualifying years to gain a full single-tier pension.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb","197416","2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49247/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49247/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49247/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to the letter dated 5 March 2014 from the Minister of State for Pensions to the hon. Member for Cardiff South and Penarth, when he plans to bring forward legislative proposals to make national insurance credits available for past periods for service spouses; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","197415"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49248","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-05-06","<p> </p><p> </p><p>Subject to Royal Assent of the Pensions Bill a duty will be placed on the Secretary of State to make regulations to allow service spouses and civil partners, due to reach State Pension age from 6 April 2016, to apply for National Insurance credits for periods during which they accompanied their husband, wife or civil partner on a posting outside the UK. The regulations will make provision to allow credits for periods between 1975/76 and 2010.</p><p> </p><p>We are working with the Ministry of Defence on the finer details of the scheme including the manner in which applications will need to be made and the precise date when the administrative arrangements will be in place.</p><p> </p><p>We estimate that up to 20,000 individuals could have a higher single-tier pension from these credits as some individuals may, at state pension age, already have sufficient qualifying years to gain a full single-tier pension.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb","197415","2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49248/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49248/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49248/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to the letter dated 5 March 2014 from the Minister of State for Pensions to the hon. Member for Cardiff South and Penarth, what estimate he has made of the number of service spouses who will be affected by his plans to bring forward legislative proposals to make national insurance credits available for past periods for service spouses.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","197416"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49249","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-06","<p>Treasury ministers meet with a range of stakeholders on an ongoing basis, including energy intensive industries. For instance the Chancellor recently visited Tata Steel's Port Talbot plant. The Chancellor has written to representatives of energy-intensive industries about the Environmental and Energy State Aid Guidelines and instructed officials to meet with them to discuss this issue.</p>","Loughborough","Nicky Morgan",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49249/answer","Biography information for Nicky Morgan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49249/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49249/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when he will next meet representatives of energy-intensive industries to discuss the EU Commission's draft Environmental and Energy State Aid Guidelines.","false","Biography information for Fiona O'Donnell","East Lothian","Fiona O'Donnell","197358"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49250","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-05-12","<p>The Department does not hold this information.</p><p> </p><p>The renewables industry, including the small and medium wind manufacturers, is an important source of jobs and investment in the UK. In 2013, Renewable UK, the trade association for the onshore wind sector, reported that the UK is home to over ten small and medium wind manufacturers and that nearly 3800 sub-15kw turbines were exported [1].</p><p> </p><p><em>[1]</em><em> R-UK Small and Medium Wind Market Report 2013 <a href="http://www.renewableuk.com/en/publications/index.cfm/Small-and-Medium-Wind-UK-Market-Report-2013" target="_blank">http://www.renewableuk.com/en/publications/index.cfm/Small-and-Medium-Wind-UK-Market-Report-2013</a></em></p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49250/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49250/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49250/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how many manufacturers of sub-15KW wind turbines are based in the UK; and what the value of exports from this sector was in 2013.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Reynolds","Stalybridge and Hyde","Jonathan Reynolds","197240"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49251","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-05-12","<p>The total spending for the Feed-in-Tariffs (FITs) scheme is set out below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><em>Year </em></p></td><td><p><em>Spending on FITs</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>Â£14,435,324.77</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>Â£150,756,063.58</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>Â£506,328,139</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>All figures are nominal, and are published in Ofgem's annual report; 2013/14 figures will be published at the end of 2014:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.ofgem.gov.uk/environmental-programmes/feed-tariff-fit-scheme/feed-tariff-reports/annual-reports" target="_blank">https://www.ofgem.gov.uk/environmental-programmes/feed-tariff-fit-scheme/feed-tariff-reports/annual-reports</a>.</p><p> </p><p>We do not publish information on spending on individual technologies within the FITs scheme, nor on spending on individual bands for each technology. More information about deployment levels of the different technologies supported by FITs is available via the link below:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/monthly-small-scale-renewable-deployment" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/monthly-small-scale-renewable-deployment</a>.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49251/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49251/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49251/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what the total cost was of support under the feed-in-tariff for (a) solar, (b) wind, (c) anaerobic digestion, (d) hydro and (e) the sub-15KW wind sector in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Reynolds","Stalybridge and Hyde","Jonathan Reynolds","197241"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49252","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-05-12","<p>As the first degression for wind tariff bands was only introduced on 1 April 2014, it is too early to say what impact it has had on manufacturing and employment in the sub-15kW wind sector. Up to the end of 2013, over 5,150 wind installations had been accredited for FITs, and this pace of deployment has shown no signs of slowing since April 2013. The degression mechanism is very important for the cost control of the FITs scheme and for keeping the cost to the electricity consumer as low as possible.</p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49252/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49252/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49252/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what assessment he has made of the effect of changes to tariff levels and degression thresholds outlined in Phase 2B of the feed-in-tariff on manufacturing and employment in the sub-15KW wind sector.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Reynolds","Stalybridge and Hyde","Jonathan Reynolds","197242"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49253","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-05-12","<p>The number of sub-15kW wind turbines accredited under the Feed-in Tariff scheme during 2012 and 2013, were 1,747 and 327 respectively.</p><p> </p><p>Installations are grouped into years based on their 'commissioning date' i.e. the date the technology was physically installed and deemed to be up and running.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49253/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49253/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49253/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how many turbines of capacity of sub-15KW were installed in (a) 2012 and (b) 2013.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Reynolds","Stalybridge and Hyde","Jonathan Reynolds","197244"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49254","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-05-06","<p> </p><p>I refer the rt. hon. Member to my answer of 1 May, <em>Official Report</em>, Column 803W.</p><p> </p>","Bristol West","Stephen Williams","197367","2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49254/answer","Biography information for Stephen Williams","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49254/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49254/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-04-30","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the reasons are for the time taken to answer question 191956 tabled for answer on 8 April 2014.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","197366"
