"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48986","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-05-07","<p>We remain extremely concerned by the ongoing situation in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) especially regarding the nuclear threat and human rights.</p><p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office's 2013 annual human rights report listed the DPRK as a country of concern. Compelling reports of widespread and systematic human rights violations, including the curtailment of fundamental freedoms and the continued use of political prison camps, are especially worrying. I met the US Special Envoy for DPRK Human Rights, Robert King, on 6 May to discuss how we can maintain international pressure on this.</p><p>The security situation remains deeply troubling. Recent statements implying that the DPRK is considering a further nuclear test, coupled with the DPRK's March decision to launch ballistic missiles in clear breach of UN Security Council Resolutions and to conduct live-fire artillery exercises, have only served to heighten tensions in the region. The UK continues to closely monitor the situation with our allies.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48986/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48986/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48986/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-04-29","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the situation in North Korea.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","197029"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48987","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-05-06","<p>Companies House confirms that since 2010, 5,308 companies have been registered in Swindon. This figure is based on company registration data from postcode areas, which can cross town boundaries, and should be considered an approximation.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48987/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48987/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48987/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-29","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many new businesses have been registered in Swindon since 2010.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","197030"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48988","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-05-07","<p>The Government offers a wide range of support to all types of businesses to start up and grow, including franchises, for example through the Growth Accelerator, the New Enterprise Allowance, mentoring and the Start Up Loan scheme.</p><p> </p><p>Women-led small and medium-sized businesses contribute around Â£82 billion to the economy. 42% of the 15,000 mentors trained through the Get Mentoring initiative are women and have contributed to the 27,000 strong mentoring network at <a href="http://www.mentorsme.co.uk/" target="_blank">www.mentorsme.co.uk</a>. The latest figures show that over 37% of Start Up Loans have gone to female entrepreneurs.</p><p> </p><p>We will continue to work closely with the Women's Business Council and others to help ensure that more women see starting and growing their own business as a real option.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48988/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48988/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48988/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-29","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps he is taking to encourage more women to franchise their businesses.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","197026"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48989","Department of Health","false","2014-05-07","<p>The UK National Screening Committee has recommended that a pilot for pulse oximetry screening for children should be set up to explore the practicalities of implementation. Ministers have accepted this advice and a pilot will commence shortly.</p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48989/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48989/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48989/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-04-29","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will take steps to extend Pulse Oximetry screening for children.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","197116"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48990","Home Office","false","2014-05-07","<p> </p><p>The Coalition Government's approach to tackling domestic violence and abuse is <br>set out in its Violence against Women and Girls Action Plan, updated in March <br>2014. It is a subject we take very seriously.<br><br>In 2013, the Home Secretary commissioned Her Majesty's Inspectorate of <br>Constabulary (HMIC) to undertake a comprehensive review on how the police deal with domestic <br>violence and abuse. HMIC's report exposed significant failings. The Home <br>Secretary is establishing a new national oversight group, which she will chair, and on which I will sit, to ensure HMIC's recommendations are acted upon. <br>The Home Secretary has also written to chief constables making it <br>clear that every police force must have an action plan in place by September <br>2014, to improve their response to domestic violence and abuse.<br><br>The Government is committed to ensuring that the police and other agencies have <br>the tools necessary to tackle domestic violence, to bring offenders to justice <br>and to ensure victims have the support they need to rebuild their lives. The <br>Government accordingly announced the national roll-out of Domestic Violence <br>Protection Orders and the Domestic Violence Disclosure Scheme <br>from 8 March 2014.</p><p> </p>","Lewes","Norman Baker",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48990/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48990/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48990/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-04-29","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent steps her Department has taken to tackle domestic abuse.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","197028"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48991","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-05-07","<p>The Department has no employees with a zero hours contract.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48991/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48991/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48991/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-04-29","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many officials in his Department are employed on zero-hours contracts.","false","Biography information for Pamela Nash","Airdrie and Shotts","Pamela Nash","107180"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48992","Home Office","false","2014-05-06","<p>The UK Border Agency was absorbed into the Home Office on 1 April 2013; its <br>successor business areas are UK Visas &amp; Immigration and Immigration Enforcement.<br><br>(i) The Home Office and its Agencies do not employ and have not employed staff <br>on zero-hours contracts. <br><br>(ii) A geographical breakdown of temporary staff employed in UK Border Agency <br>successor business areas in each of the last two years is shown at Table 1.</p><p>[ATTACH TABLE]</p><p><br>NOTE: Office for National Statistics defines temporary staff as those civil <br>servants with contracts of employment of less than one year; staff with Fixed <br>Term Appointments and Permanent staff are reported separately by all government <br>departments, as are Agency and Contingent Workers.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48992/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48992/answer","PQ 107079 Table 1 V1.xlsx","PQ 107079 Table 1 V1.xlsx","TABLE 1","TABLE 1","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48992/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-04-29","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many UK Border Agency staff in (a) Scotland, (b) England, (c) Wales, (d) Northern Ireland and (e) the UK were (i) on zero-hours contracts and (ii) temporary staff in each of the last two years up to the most recent period for which records are available.","false","Biography information for Pamela Nash","Airdrie and Shotts","Pamela Nash","107179"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48993","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-05-06","<p /> <p /> <p>Information on the amount of child maintenance arrears owed by (a) UK parliamentary constituency will be placed in the Library.</p><p> </p><p>The information on child maintenance arrears by (b) local authority area is already published and can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/284686/csa_qtr_summ_stats_regional_dec13.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/284686/csa_qtr_summ_stats_regional_dec13.xls</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Notes:</p><p>The table contains outstanding arrears figures as at December 2012 and December 2013 broken down by each local authority. Although arrears figures are available in previously published versions of the regional tables (available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/child-support-agency-quarterly-summary-statistics--2" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/child-support-agency-quarterly-summary-statistics--2</a>) these figures are not comparable due to a different methodology.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48993/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48993/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48993/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-04-29","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much remains outstanding in child maintenance arrears by (a) UK parliamentary constituency area and (b) local authority area in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Pamela Nash","Airdrie and Shotts","Pamela Nash","197190"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48994","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-05-07","<p> </p><p>We are currently working with a range of representatives from across the sector to identify the most effective mechanism for distributing the Â£16.6 million over 2014/15 â 2015/16 across local government to help local government combat fraud. We intend to make an announcement about our plans for this investment later in the spring.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48994/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48994/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48994/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-04-29","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when he expects to announce the allocation of additional support to local authorities in England to support corporate counter-fraud activity.","false","Biography information for Andy Sawford","Corby","Andy Sawford","197204"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48995","Department of Health","false","2014-05-07","<p>No recent central assessment has been made of the level of support available for people with Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder. Such assessments are conducted at a local level as part of any local area's Joint Strategic Needs Assessment (JSNA). JSNAs are the means by which local leaders work together to understand and agree the needs of all local people, with the joint health and wellbeing strategy setting the priorities for collective action. Clinical commissioning groups are then responsible for commissioning services to meet the assessed needs of the local population they serve.</p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48995/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48995/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48995/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-04-29","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent assessment he has made of the level of support available for sufferers of post-traumatic stress disorder.","false","Biography information for Mr Mike Hancock","Portsmouth South","Mr Mike Hancock","196991"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48996","Department of Health","false","2014-05-07","<p>Estimates of the fraction of mortality in English local authority areas and regions in 2010 and 2011 attributable to long-term exposure to particulate air pollution arising from human activities are published by Public Health England (PHE) as one of the indicators in the Department of Health's Public Health Outcomes Framework. For Portsmouth Unitary Authority this figure was 5.9% in both 2010 and 2011; for Hampshire County Council this figure was 5.3% in 2010 and 5.4% in 2011; and for the South East this figure was 5.5% in both 2010 and 2011.</p><p> </p><p>PHE has also published mortality estimates for 2010 as attributable deaths[1] and associated years of life lost. The estimated mortality burdens attributable to long-term exposure to particulate air pollution arising from human activities were: 95 attributable deaths and 1059 associated years of life lost in Portsmouth Unitary Authority; 601 attributable deaths and 6211 associated years of life lost in Hampshire County Council; and 4,034 attributable deaths and 41,729 associated years of life lost in the South East.</p><p> </p><p>[1] The ânumber of deaths' attributable to a risk factor is a metric which is widely used in communicating about public health risks. Nonetheless, a calculated figure of âattributable deaths' does not represent the number of individuals whose length of life has been shortened by air pollution. Long-term exposure to air pollution is understood to be a contributory factor to deaths from respiratory and, particularly, cardiovascular disease, ie unlikely to be the sole cause of deaths of individuals. This means that it is likely that air pollution contributes a smaller amount to the deaths of a larger number of exposed individuals rather than being solely responsible for a number of deaths equivalent to the calculated figure of âattributable deaths'. The distribution of the mortality effect within the population is unknown.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48996/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48996/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48996/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-04-29","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the number of deaths  in (a) Portsmouth, (b) Hampshire and (c) the South East attributed to air pollution in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Mr Mike Hancock","Portsmouth South","Mr Mike Hancock","196992"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48997","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-05-08","<p>Although mental health problems, and PTSD in particular, are no more prevalent amongst Service personnel than the broader civilian population, it is recognised that Service personnel who do experience mental health problems may find it harder to make the transition to civilian life. <br><br>The Government has therefore given priority to ensuring that Service leavers and veterans can access timely and appropriate mental health treatment, should it be necessary, both in the NHS and through other programmes delivered across Government and the voluntary sector. All of the recommendations of the âFighting Fit' report, written by the now Minister for International Security Strategy (Dr Murrison), have been implemented.<br><br>Examples of initiatives taken forward under this Government include Structured Mental Health assessment as part of routine and discharge medicals; specialist follow-on treatment after discharge; the introduction of e-learning packages for clinicians, providing information and advice on the healthcare needs of the Armed Forces, their families and veterans; funding for the Combat Stress 24 hr Mental Health Helpline; and the introduction of the Big White Wall, providing Mental Health wellbeing services to serving personnel, their families and veterans.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48997/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48997/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48997/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48997/answer/previousversion/9120","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-04-29","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent assessment he has made of the effect of post-traumatic stress disorder on the ability of former services personnel to reintegrate into civilian life.","false","Biography information for Mr Mike Hancock","Portsmouth South","Mr Mike Hancock","196990"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48998","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-05-06","<p>There have been almost 11,500 responses to the consultation on the future of civil partnership in England and Wales. We are now considering them and will publish a summary in due course.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant","197112","2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48998/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48998/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48998/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-04-29","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many responses were received to his Department's consultation on extending civil partnerships to opposite sex couples.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","197111"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48999","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-05-06","<p>There have been almost 11,500 responses to the consultation on the future of civil partnership in England and Wales. We are now considering them and will publish a summary in due course.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant","197111","2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48999/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48999/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48999/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-04-29","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, when he plans to publish the responses to the consultation on extending civil partnerships to opposite sex couples.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","197112"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49000","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-05-06","<p>The Government is currently considering the views expressed by consultation respondents on the future of civil partnership in England and Wales. The Government has not itself proposed any changes to civil partnership.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49000/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49000/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49000/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-04-29","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, when he plans to bring forward legislative proposals to extend civil partnerships to opposite sex couples.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","197113"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49001","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-05-06","<p>On 23 January 2014, when the consultation document was published, I made a Ministerial Written Statement to bring it to the attention of honourable members. This statement was repeated in the House of Lords, by my colleague, Baroness Northover. The publication of the consultation was also announced on the Culture, Media and Sport website. DCMS officials directly contacted around 50 organisations with an interest in the issues and asked other Departments to do the same. Officials also offered meetings to the principal stakeholders, several of which took up the offer, and emailed more than 1300 organisations and individuals who had registered an interest in receiving updates on equal marriage or related issues and highlighted the consultation in the February edition of the Women's Engagement Newsletter, which is circulated to more than 2000 organisations and individuals.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant","197115","2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49001/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49001/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49001/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-04-29","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he took to publicise the consultation on extending civil partnerships to opposite sex partners.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","197114"
